wiki.summary: Huntin' Wabbitz is the fourth song on J. Cole’s “Might Delete Later” project. It was produced by T-Minus, Charlie Heat and Ibrahim Hamad who is also the co-founder of J. Cole’s Dreamville. The song features psychadelic production and laid-back, relaxed bars from Cole. The song samples sections from “Wabbit Season”, which is a popular video created by YouTuber MeatCanyon, who is known for creating funny, but disturbing videos. “Wabbit Season” is MeatCanyon’s interpretation of Looney Tunes. wiki.content: Huntin' Wabbitz is the fourth song on J. Cole’s “Might Delete Later” project. It was produced by T-Minus, Charlie Heat and Ibrahim Hamad who is also the co-founder of J. Cole’s Dreamville. The song features psychadelic production and laid-back, relaxed bars from Cole. The song samples sections from “Wabbit Season”, which is a popular video created by YouTuber MeatCanyon, who is known for creating funny, but disturbing videos. “Wabbit Season” is MeatCanyon’s interpretation of Looney Tunes. The instrumental of Huntin' Wabbitz also includes a sample from the Italian composition “La modella” (1969), written by Giuseppe De Luca with vocals by Nora Orlandi, originally composed for the soundtrack of the Italian film “L'altra faccia del peccato”. “La modella” comes from the catalog of CAM Sugar, an Italian label renowned for its archive of classic Italian film music, frequently selected for sampling in rap music.
